
% ===== Results (auto-wired for tables/figures) =====

\section{Results}

\subsection{Study selection}
Screening identified controlled trials of MDMA, LSD, psilocybin, and ayahuasca that reported adverse events in at least one acute \emph{session} window and/or a subsequent \emph{follow-up} window. Details of eligibility and reference-arm selection are described in Methods.

\subsection{Study characteristics}
Across molecules, trials included one to six active dose tiers and an inactive placebo (when available). Adverse events (AEs) were harmonised to a shared vocabulary (\texttt{ae\_term}) and analysed by time window (session vs follow-up). A compact summary per molecule, including significance counts, is provided in \Cref{tab:topline-summary}.

\IfFileExists{tables/compare_topline_molecule.tex}{%
  \begin{table}[ht]
    \centering
    \caption{Topline significance summary per molecule (session and follow-up).}
    \label{tab:topline-summary}
    \input{tables/compare_topline_molecule.tex}
  \end{table}
}{}

\subsection{Primary synthesis of adverse events}
Random-effects pooling showed molecule-specific AE profiles during the acute session, with markedly fewer signals at follow-up. Per-molecule aggregate statistics (including $k$, $I^2$, $\tau^2$, and overall p-values) are shown in \Cref{tab:overall-by-molecule}.

\IfFileExists{tables/compare_by_molecule_overall.tex}{%
  \begin{table}[ht]
    \centering
    \caption{Overall pooled statistics per molecule (session and follow-up).}
    \label{tab:overall-by-molecule}
    \input{tables/compare_by_molecule_overall.tex}
  \end{table}
}{}

